  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering penalties can include:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties:\n- Potential prison sentences of up to 20 years\n- Significant fines (often up to $500,000 or double the value of the property involved)\n- Criminal forfeiture of assets\n\n2. Civil Penalties:\n- Monetary civil penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential additional financial sanctions\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like the amount of money involved, specific circumstances, and whether it's a first-time or repeat offense. Prosecution typically occurs through statutes like the Bank Secrecy Act and Title 18 of the U.S. Code.\n\nExact sentencing can vary based on individual case details and judicial discretion.",
